Firewalls:
 added in order to manage incoming traffic to the 3 servers and provide security

1 SSL certificate for load balancer:
in order to acheive secure transmission between the 3 servers and the users using the HTTPs protocol

Monitoring Client:
to order the view and monitor the health and the usage of the 3 severs and provide alerts in specific cases


How do Monitoring tools collect the data?
Some monitoring tools use lightweight software agents installed on each monitored system. These agents continuously collect performance metrics, logs, and other relevant data from the local system.
Agents may gather information such as CPU usage, memory utilization, disk I/O, network traffic, application performance metrics, and log entries.

Explain what to do if you want to monitor your web server QPS:
To monitor your web server's QPS (Queries Per Second), you'll need to set up monitoring tools or systems that can collect and analyze relevant metrics from your web server.
you'll need to:
select the tools
installs agents if needed 
configure data collection
monitor QPS metrics
Set alerts

